<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="3" type="reference_group">
<paragraph pageId="2" pageNumber="3">
<taxonomicName authority="Bilberg, 1820" authorityName="Liston &amp; Goergen &amp; Koch" authorityYear="2017" class="Insecta" family="Argidae" genus="Sterictophora" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Sterictophora" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="comb. n.">Sterictophora</taxonomicName>
[sic] 
<taxonomicName authority="Bilberg, 1820" authorityName="Liston &amp; Goergen &amp; Koch" authorityYear="2017" class="Insecta" family="Argidae" genus="Sterictophora" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="afra" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="afra" status="comb. n.">afra</taxonomicName>
Pasteels, 1963: 540-541. Described: male (holotype, MNCN). Type locality: 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“Cameroun”">&quot;Cameroun&quot;</normalizedToken>
(Cameroon). Images of holotype and labels by A. Taeger: http://dx.doi.org/10.6084/m9.figshare.746940.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="3" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="2" pageNumber="3">
<taxonomicName authority="Billberg, 1820" authorityName="Billberg" authorityYear="1820" class="Insecta" family="Argidae" genus="Sterictiphora" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Sterictiphora afra" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="afra">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Sterictiphora afra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Pasteels, 1963 has been regarded as the only Afrotropical species of 
<taxonomicName authority="Billberg, 1820" authorityName="Billberg" authorityYear="1820" class="Insecta" family="Argidae" genus="Sterictiphora" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Sterictiphora" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Sterictiphora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, an otherwise Holarctic and Oriental genus. The holotype (examined) is the only known specimen of the species. It is labelled &quot;Kamerun 1898&quot;, in the same handwriting as on the label attached to the type of 
<taxonomicName authority="" authorityName="" class="Insecta" family="Megalodontesidae" genus="Clyparge" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Clyparge terminalis" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="terminalis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Clyparge terminalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.3790.1.5" author="Taeger, A" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" pagination="103 - 138" refId="B43" refString="Taeger, A, Paris, M, Nieves-Aldrey, JL, 2014. The type specimens of sawflies (Hymenoptera: Symphyta) of the Museo Nacional de Ciencias Naturales, Madrid. Zootaxa 3790 (1): 103 - 138, DOI: https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.3790.1.5" title="The type specimens of sawflies (Hymenoptera: Symphyta) of the Museo Nacional de Ciencias Naturales, Madrid." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.3790.1.5" volume="3790" year="2014">Taeger et al. 2014</bibRefCitation>
): see under that name above. In the keys by 
<bibRefCitation author="Koch, F" journalOrPublisher="Staatliches Museum fuer Tierkunde in Dresden" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" pagination="29 - 61" refId="B12" refString="Koch, F, 1988. Die Gattung Sterictiphora Billberg (Insecta, Hymenoptera, Symphyta: Argidae). Entomologische Abhandlungen. Staatliches Museum fuer Tierkunde in Dresden 52 (2): 29 - 61" title="Die Gattung Sterictiphora Billberg (Insecta, Hymenoptera, Symphyta: Argidae). Entomologische Abhandlungen." volume="52" year="1988">Koch (1988)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Smith, DR" journalOrPublisher="Transactions of the American Entomological Society" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" pagination="537 - 594" publicationUrl="jstor.org" refId="B39" refString="Smith, DR, 1971. Nearctic sawflies of the genera Neoptilia Ashmead, Schizocerella Forsius, Aprosthema Konow, and Sphacophilus Provancher (Hymenoptera: Argidae). Transactions of the American Entomological Society 97: 537 - 594, jstor.org" title="Nearctic sawflies of the genera Neoptilia Ashmead, Schizocerella Forsius, Aprosthema Konow, and Sphacophilus Provancher (Hymenoptera: Argidae)." url="jstor.org" volume="97" year="1971">Smith (1971</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Smith, DR" journalOrPublisher="Memoirs of the American Entomological Society" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" pagination="1 - 201" publicationUrl="researchgate.net" refId="B41" refString="Smith, DR, 1992. A synopsis of the sawflies (Hymenoptera: Symphyta) of America south of the United States: Argidae. Memoirs of the American Entomological Society 39: 1 - 201, researchgate.net" title="A synopsis of the sawflies (Hymenoptera: Symphyta) of America south of the United States: Argidae." url="researchgate.net" volume="39" year="1992">1992</bibRefCitation>
), 
<taxonomicName authority="Billberg, 1820" authorityName="Billberg" authorityYear="1820" class="Insecta" family="Argidae" genus="Sterictiphora" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Sterictiphora afra" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="afra">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Sterictiphora afra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
runs without problem to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Provancher" authorityYear="1888" class="Insecta" family="Argidae" genus="Sphacophilus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Sphacophilus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Sphacophilus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Provancher, 1888. This genus contains about 50 valid species, distributed in the Neotropical and Nearctic Regions. Species taxonomy of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Provancher" authorityYear="1888" class="Insecta" family="Argidae" genus="Sphacophilus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Sphacophilus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Sphacophilus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is based mainly on females, and males of many species are unknown, or the association of the sexes is problematic (
<bibRefCitation author="Smith, DR" journalOrPublisher="Memoirs of the American Entomological Society" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" pagination="1 - 201" publicationUrl="researchgate.net" refId="B41" refString="Smith, DR, 1992. A synopsis of the sawflies (Hymenoptera: Symphyta) of America south of the United States: Argidae. Memoirs of the American Entomological Society 39: 1 - 201, researchgate.net" title="A synopsis of the sawflies (Hymenoptera: Symphyta) of America south of the United States: Argidae." url="researchgate.net" volume="39" year="1992">Smith 1992</bibRefCitation>
). We were unable to identify the holotype of 
<taxonomicName authority="Billberg, 1820" authorityName="Billberg" authorityYear="1820" class="Insecta" family="Argidae" genus="Sterictiphora" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Sterictiphora afra" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="afra">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Sterictiphora afra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to species level, using the keys by 
<bibRefCitation author="Smith, DR" journalOrPublisher="Transactions of the American Entomological Society" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" pagination="537 - 594" publicationUrl="jstor.org" refId="B39" refString="Smith, DR, 1971. Nearctic sawflies of the genera Neoptilia Ashmead, Schizocerella Forsius, Aprosthema Konow, and Sphacophilus Provancher (Hymenoptera: Argidae). Transactions of the American Entomological Society 97: 537 - 594, jstor.org" title="Nearctic sawflies of the genera Neoptilia Ashmead, Schizocerella Forsius, Aprosthema Konow, and Sphacophilus Provancher (Hymenoptera: Argidae)." url="jstor.org" volume="97" year="1971">Smith (1971</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Smith, DR" journalOrPublisher="Memoirs of the American Entomological Society" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" pagination="1 - 201" publicationUrl="researchgate.net" refId="B41" refString="Smith, DR, 1992. A synopsis of the sawflies (Hymenoptera: Symphyta) of America south of the United States: Argidae. Memoirs of the American Entomological Society 39: 1 - 201, researchgate.net" title="A synopsis of the sawflies (Hymenoptera: Symphyta) of America south of the United States: Argidae." url="researchgate.net" volume="39" year="1992">1992</bibRefCitation>
) and reference to several original descriptions. However, the colour pattern of the 
<taxonomicName authority="Billberg, 1820" authorityName="Billberg" authorityYear="1820" class="Insecta" family="Argidae" genus="Sterictiphora" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Sterictiphora afra" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="afra">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Sterictiphora afra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
holotype is distinctive within this genus. Apart from the recently described 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Smith &amp; Morales-Reyes" authorityYear="2015" class="Insecta" family="Argidae" genus="Sphacophilus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Sphacophilus monjarasi" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="monjarasi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Sphacophilus monjarasi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Smith &amp; Morales-Reyes, 2015 (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.4289/0013-8797.117.2.179" author="Monjaras-Barrera, JI" journalOrPublisher="Proceedings of the Entomological Society of Washington" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" pagination="179 - 182" refId="B28" refString="Monjaras-Barrera, JI, Morales-Reyes, C, Smith, DR, 2015. A new species of Sphacophilus (Hymenoptera: Argidae) from Mexico feeding on Chipilin, Crotalaria longirostrata (Fabaceae). Proceedings of the Entomological Society of Washington 117 (2): 179 - 182, DOI: https://doi.org/10.4289/0013-8797.117.2.179" title="A new species of Sphacophilus (Hymenoptera: Argidae) from Mexico feeding on Chipilin, Crotalaria longirostrata (Fabaceae)." url="https://doi.org/10.4289/0013-8797.117.2.179" volume="117" year="2015">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Monjarás-Barrera">Monjaras-Barrera</normalizedToken>
et al. 2015
</bibRefCitation>
), no other known species has this combination of completely black head and thorax, including the entire legs, and an almost completely yellow abdomen. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Smith &amp; Morales-Reyes" authorityYear="2015" class="Insecta" family="Argidae" genus="Sphacophilus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Sphacophilus monjarasi" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="monjarasi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Sphacophilus monjarasi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is unfortunately only known in the female sex. Its type locality is in Chiapas Province, Mexico. In view of the lack of any other evidence for its presence in the Afrotropics, we recommend that 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Liston &amp; Goergen &amp; Koch" authorityYear="2017" baseAuthorityName="Pasteels" baseAuthorityYear="1963" class="Insecta" family="Argidae" genus="Sphacophilus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Sphacophilus afer" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="afer">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Sphacophilus afer</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, simultaneously the only representative of the 
<taxonomicName lsidName="" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Sterictiphorinae">Sterictiphorinae</taxonomicName>
there, should be removed from the list of Afrotropical sawflies.
</paragraph>
